O laal meri pat rakhio bhala jhoole laalan, Sindri da Sehvan da, sakhi Shabaaz kalandar, Dama dam mast kalandar, Ali dam dam de andar, Ali da pehla number

O, the red-robed, please do grant me your kind protection, the red-robed Lord!

O, the Lord, the benefactor of Sindh and Sehwan(both in current day Pakistan), the friend Shahbaaz Qalandar(most respected preacher, holy man, considered divine spirit), the Almighty in every breath of yours, glory unto to you! God be great!

snippet.textDisplay: Who is the poet reciting the verses...waah! Rongte khade ho gayein...I learned this song in the early 70s when Runa Laila sang it on Doordarshan in India and was instantly smitten. I sang it so often that one of my friends referred to me as the Mast Qalandar girl;-) After 43 years that is a huge compliment! But Qurat-ul-ain Balouch has taken this to a new level...singing away again!
